There once was a perfect world, where mankind had vanquished death itself, living in endless life and boundless harmony. Yet, to balance life's precious gift, a revered order of Scythes was born, tasked with the grim duty of gleaning, for only they could bring true demise. Two young souls, Citra Terranova and Rowan Damisch, were unexpectedly chosen by a wise and honorable Scythe to undertake this fearsome apprenticeship. Though neither desired the burden of taking life, they were thrust into a world of rigorous training and dark philosophy. For only one could prevail and become a Scythe, and the dire decree held that the victor's first task would be to glean the vanquished, thus forcing them into an impossible, mortal choice.
